06:05.990 --> 06:09.560
An overworked
and under-appreciated housewife

06:09.630 --> 06:12.640
has snapped and parked her
car on the bridge,
refusing to budge.

06:12.700 --> 06:15.710
This reporter is now
going to be lowered down
in the Channel 6 sky harness

06:15.770 --> 06:17.610
for an exclusive interview.

06:18.810 --> 06:20.280
Huh?

06:21.510 --> 06:22.550
Ow!

06:22.610 --> 06:24.080
Hey!

06:24.150 --> 06:25.820
Ow!

06:27.420 --> 06:29.320
Hey sweetheart,
what's the matter?

06:29.380 --> 06:31.650
Not getting enough
of the good stuff at home?

06:33.890 --> 06:34.760
D-ohh!

06:38.390 --> 06:39.150
( <i>bystanders talking )</i>

06:39.230 --> 06:40.530
Let me through.

06:40.600 --> 06:41.670
I'm her husband.

06:41.730 --> 06:43.230
That explains a lot.

06:43.300 --> 06:44.570
( <i>both chuckling )</i>

06:44.630 --> 06:45.730
( <i>both sighing )</i>

06:45.800 --> 06:47.470
Try to talk her
out of there

06:47.540 --> 06:49.240
but don't put
your lips on it
or anything.

06:49.300 --> 06:50.230
Hello.

06:50.310 --> 06:52.080
Hello!

06:52.140 --> 06:53.080
Is this thing on?

06:53.140 --> 06:53.810
Hello?!

06:53.880 --> 06:55.250
Homer, is that you?

06:55.310 --> 06:56.450
What should I say?

06:56.510 --> 06:58.150
Well how about,
"Yes, it's me"?

06:58.210 --> 06:59.470
Yes, it's me.

06:59.550 --> 07:01.150
Tell her you love her.

07:01.220 --> 07:02.890
I love you very much.

07:02.950 --> 07:04.160
Crowd:
Awww.

07:04.220 --> 07:05.560
And, uh...

07:05.620 --> 07:08.490
later tonight,
I think you and I should, uh...

07:08.560 --> 07:09.890
snuggle?

07:09.960 --> 07:12.560
( <i>laughing )</i>

07:12.630 --> 07:13.700
Ha, ha!

07:13.760 --> 07:16.730
Uh, why don't you
just wrap it up?

07:16.800 --> 07:20.400
Look Marge, I can tell
something's bothering you

07:20.470 --> 07:22.210
but if you come out
of that car

07:22.270 --> 07:23.210
I promise to do
whatever it takes

07:23.270 --> 07:24.480
to make it better.

07:24.540 --> 07:26.610
Please, honey?

07:26.680 --> 07:28.210
Okay.

07:34.420 --> 07:35.620
Cuff her, boys!

07:44.260 --> 07:45.500
Off the record, ma'am

07:45.560 --> 07:47.530
all the gals on the force

07:47.600 --> 07:49.170
- knew just how you felt.
- That's nice.

07:49.230 --> 07:50.900
Do you think you could
loosen my cuffs?

07:50.970 --> 07:52.070
No.

07:52.130 --> 07:54.060
Don't you
worry, Mr. Mayor.

07:54.140 --> 07:56.710
This little bird'll
be cracking rocks by the
end of the week.

07:56.770 --> 07:58.540
Wiggum, you
glorified night watchman

07:58.610 --> 07:59.240
let her go!

07:59.310 --> 08:00.380
But she broke the law.

08:00.440 --> 08:02.380
Thanks for the civics lesson.

08:02.440 --> 08:04.310
Now listen to me.
If Marge Simpson goes to jail

08:04.380 --> 08:06.520
I can kiss the chick vote
good-bye

08:06.580 --> 08:09.350
and if I go down,
you're gonna break my fall!

08:09.420 --> 08:12.720
Word to the wise, Quimby.
Don't write checks
your butt can't cash.

08:12.790 --> 08:15.430
Hear me loud and clear Wiggum,
you bite me, I'll bite back.

08:15.490 --> 08:18.560
You talk the talk, Quimby,
but do you walk the walk?

08:18.630 --> 08:22.400
I hereby declare today
to be Marge Simpson Day

08:22.460 --> 08:24.260
in the city of Springfield.

08:24.330 --> 08:25.130
( <i>cheering )</i>

08:27.200 --> 08:29.210
They're like trained seals--
toss 'em a fish

08:29.270 --> 08:31.310
and watch 'em slap
their fins together.

08:33.640 --> 08:37.150
Well, all's well
that ends well.

08:37.210 --> 08:40.720
Good night, Marge.

08:40.780 --> 08:42.510
( <i>snoring )</i>

08:42.580 --> 08:44.210
( <i>growls )</i>

08:44.290 --> 08:46.160
<i>Many years ago</i>

08:46.220 --> 08:49.160
<i>the Spanish explorers
discovered their little
piece of heaven</i>

08:49.220 --> 08:51.290
<i>nestled in the
Springfield mountains.</i>

08:51.360 --> 08:53.060
<i>They called it Rancho Relaxo</i>

08:53.130 --> 08:54.770
<i>and so do we.</i>

08:54.830 --> 08:58.370
