is only 14 calories.

13:14.460 --> 13:15.930
( <i>moaning )</i>

13:15.990 --> 13:17.490
Oh, Gregory...

13:17.560 --> 13:19.800
where have you been
all my life?

13:19.860 --> 13:21.070
( <i>laughs )</i>

13:21.130 --> 13:22.400
Feeling tense?

13:22.460 --> 13:23.190
Uh-huh.

13:23.260 --> 13:24.760
Then just push nine

13:24.830 --> 13:26.330
on your phone

13:26.400 --> 13:29.340
then the pound sign,
then 4-8-3.

13:29.400 --> 13:30.730
We'll do the rest.

13:30.810 --> 13:34.140
( <i>moans )</i>

13:34.210 --> 13:35.580
Homer:
<i>Come on, Maggie.</i>

13:35.640 --> 13:36.570
<i>Nummy-nummy-num.</i>

13:40.780 --> 13:43.950
Mmm-mm!

13:44.020 --> 13:45.960
Mmm. Strained peas.

13:46.020 --> 13:49.090
( <i>to tune of "Rule Brittania":)
♪ Shakespeare's fried chicken ♪</i>

13:49.160 --> 13:50.730
♪ Come gorge yourself today... ♪

13:51.960 --> 13:53.400
( <i>grunting )</i>

13:56.200 --> 13:58.300
♪ Nyah-nyah, nyah-nyah,
la, la, la... ♪

13:58.370 --> 13:59.470
( <i>growling )</i>

13:59.530 --> 14:00.900
( <i>yelling )</i>

14:00.970 --> 14:02.940
D-ohhh! Let go!

14:03.000 --> 14:04.570
Mmmmm...

14:04.640 --> 14:06.140
Ohh... ahh...

14:06.210 --> 14:08.050
Marge,
it's times like this

14:08.110 --> 14:11.520
I'm glad I flunked out
of that Mexican med school.

14:11.580 --> 14:12.650
Hi, Barney.

14:12.710 --> 14:14.810
Thanks for keeping
me company.

14:14.880 --> 14:15.810
No problem.

14:15.880 --> 14:17.180
Well, well.

14:17.250 --> 14:19.660
If it isn't little Bart.

14:19.720 --> 14:21.590
Remember
your Uncle Barney?

14:21.660 --> 14:23.660
Hey, Homer,
let me hold him.

14:23.730 --> 14:25.930
All right,
but just be careful.

14:25.990 --> 14:29.660
Whoa! Someone smells stinky.

14:29.730 --> 14:30.800
( <i>sniffs )</i>

14:30.870 --> 14:31.740
Oh, it's me.

14:33.000 --> 14:33.940
Bart

14:34.000 --> 14:34.810
you really shouldn't be looking

14:34.870 --> 14:36.470
through other people's things.

14:37.610 --> 14:38.940
Find anything good?

14:39.010 --> 14:41.180
I said it before,
and I'll say it again.

14:41.240 --> 14:42.070
<i>Ay, caramba!</i>

14:43.610 --> 14:45.120
Hey, Lise, bang, bang!

14:45.180 --> 14:46.180
Aw, Bart...

14:46.250 --> 14:47.820
that's a blackhead gun!

14:47.880 --> 14:48.710
Eww!

14:52.120 --> 14:53.990
Best <i>McGyver ever.</i>

14:54.060 --> 14:55.490
Mm-hmm.

14:55.560 --> 14:59.330
Richard Dean Anderson
will be in my dreams tonight.

14:59.390 --> 15:03.190
( <i>loud, obnoxious snoring )</i>

15:08.040 --> 15:09.910
( <i>shuddering groans )</i>

15:13.710 --> 15:16.510
( <i>sighs )</i>

15:16.580 --> 15:18.620
Homer:
<i>♪ Go to sleep ♪</i>

15:18.680 --> 15:20.720
♪ and good night ♪

15:20.780 --> 15:25.020
♪ La-da-da-da, da-da-da ♪

15:25.090 --> 15:27.020
♪ dee-dee-dee ♪

15:27.090 --> 15:29.530
♪ dee-dee-dee ♪

15:29.590 --> 15:34.470
♪ may your Christmas days
be nice. ♪

15:34.530 --> 15:36.900
Good night, my little pork chop.

15:49.880 --> 15:51.680
( <i>Barney snoring )</i>

15:56.680 --> 15:57.980
( <i>belches )</i>

16:19.370 --> 16:20.300
Oh, Maggie?

16:20.380 --> 16:22.810
Time for your 9:00 a.m. feeding.

16:22.880 --> 16:23.910
Heh, heh, heh.

16:28.280 --> 16:29.010
( <i>screams )</i>

16:30.850 --> 16:32.460
Maggie?

16:32.520 --> 16:33.120
Maggie?

16:34.290 --> 16:36.530
Maggie?!

16:36.590 --> 16:37.190
( <i>snoring )</i>

16:37.260 --> 16:38.330
Oh... hoo...

16:38.390 --> 16:40.320
( <i>grunting )</i>

16:40.400 --> 16:41.370
Maggie!

16:41.430 --> 16:42.330
Oh, man.

16:42.400 --> 16:44.540
You want a bad night?

16:44.600 --> 16:45.240
Try sleeping

16:45.300 --> 16:46.700
on one of these.

16:46.770 --> 16:47.910
Barney,
I've lost the baby.

16:47.970 --> 16:50.170
It's the worst thing
I've ever done.

16:50.240 --> 16:51.410
Don't worry.

16:51.470 --> 16:53.070
You know what
I'm going to do?

16:53.140 --> 16:54.850
I'm going to make you
an omelet.

16:54.910 --> 16:56.050
Just help me look.

16:56.110 --> 16:57.480
Are you sure?

16:57.550 --> 16:59.780
- I make them
with two kinds of cheese.
- C'mon!

17:00.980 --> 17:03.190
Homer, I think
I've got her.

17:03.250 --> 17:04.220
( <i>grunting )</i>

17:04.290 --> 17:05.819
Come on!

17:05.890 --> 17:08.260
Barney, you're gonna
pull her arm off!

17:08.319 --> 17:09.920
The sooner
I get her out

17:09.990 --> 17:12.160
the sooner
we can have omelets.

17:12.230 --> 17:13.030
( <i>grunts )</i>

17:27.310 --> 17:29.650
( <i>sighs )</i>

17:29.710 --> 17:30.810
Hmm, so, what's
the verdict?

17:30.880 --> 17:32.280
Oh, dear God.

17:32.350 --> 17:34.890
I can't even put a bag
over my head.

17:34.950 --> 17:36.150
Yes, you can.

17:39.020 --> 17:41.590
Hello, I'd like the department
of missing babies.

17:41.660 --> 17:42.760
Man:
Please hold.

17:42.820 --> 17:43.980
♪ <i>Baby, come back ♪</i>

17:44.060 --> 17:45.160
♪ listen, baby ♪

17:45.230 --> 17:48.430
♪ <i>You can blame it all on me ♪</i>

17:48.500 --> 17:53.640
♪ <i>I was wrong, and I just
can't live without you... ♪</i>

17:58.710 --> 18:01.350
Hmm, I guess
I've done everything.

18:04.880 --> 18:08.050
By now you've seen
what Rancho Relaxo has to offer.

18:08.120 --> 18:09.720
Uh-huh.

18:09.780 --> 18:12.310
But remember, we can't tell
you how to have a good time.

18:12.390 --> 18:13.790
You have to tell us.

18:13.860 --> 18:14.690
Oh.

18:14.760 --> 18:16.060
As I said

18:16.120 --> 18:19.120
to Delores Montenegro
in <i>Calling All Quakers...</i>

18:19.190 --> 18:21.120
"Have it <i>your way, baby."</i>

18:21.200 --> 18:25.140
( <i>corny theme music )</i>

18:25.200 --> 18:27.300
Hello, room service?

18:27.370 --> 18:29.210
This is Marge Simpson.

18:29.270 --> 18:32.310
I'd like a hot fudge sundae
with whipped cream

18:32.370 --> 18:35.100
and some
chocolate chip cheesecake

18:35.180 --> 18:37.780
and a bottle of tequila.

18:37.850 --> 18:40.450
<i>Let's get out of here, Thelma.</i>

18:40.520 --> 18:41.690
<i>Okay, Louise.</i>

18:42.920 --> 18:50.230
( <i>long, deep sigh )</i>

18:56.900 --> 18:58.500
What do <i>you want?</i>

18:58.570 --> 19:00.540
I came to see the kids.

19:00.600 --> 19:01.610
Wait here...

19:01.670 --> 19:03.440
and don't steal
any light bulbs.

19:03.500 --> 19:05.270
Hmm...

19:05.340 --> 19:06.440
Dad!
Dad!

19:06.510 --> 19:07.740
Hey, kids.

19:07.810 --> 19:10.910
You haven't seen Maggie
around anyplace, have you?

19:10.980 --> 19:12.820
Hmm-mm.
Hmm-mm.

19:12.880 --> 19:15.320
Oh... well, I got to go.

19:17.990 --> 19:19.690
Patty:
Come on, kids.

19:19.750 --> 19:21.080
It's time to rub
Aunt Patty's feet.

19:21.160 --> 19:23.590
( <i>shuddering groans )</i>

19:26.390 --> 19:28.490
( <i>southern accent: )
Hello, Gov'nor.</i>

19:28.560 --> 19:30.260
Lube job while you wait?

19:30.330 --> 19:31.340
Don't touch me.

19:36.900 --> 19:38.170
( <i>sobbing )</i>

19:38.240 --> 19:39.110
( <i>phone ringing )</i>

19:39.170 --> 19:40.130
Yello.

19:40.210 --> 19:41.110
Hi, Homey.

19:41.180 --> 19:43.110
I feel much better.

19:43.180 --> 19:45.520
Listen, Marge... uh...

19:45.580 --> 19:48.850
how would you feel
if I told you the dog ran away?

19:48.920 --> 19:50.250
Homer, that's awful.

19:50.320 --> 19:52.120
Oh. Well, I got
good news for you.

19:52.190 --> 19:53.820
The dog didn't run away.

19:53.890 --> 19:54.830
Well, good.

19:54.890 --> 19:56.560
I'm coming home, honey.

19:56.620 --> 19:58.650
You can pick me up at the
train station in an hour

19:58.730 --> 19:59.560
<i>and bring the kids.</i>

19:59.630 --> 20:00.960
<i>Bye.</i>

20:01.030 --> 20:03.430
D-ohhh!

20:03.500 --> 20:04.870
Please, don't jump.

20:04.930 --> 20:07.630
I know you're going through
some tough times

20:07.700 --> 20:10.570
but you have your whole life
ahead of you.

20:12.410 --> 20:14.910
Well, Marge...
Maggie was very young.

20:14.980 --> 20:17.710
It's not like we got
so attached to her.

20:17.780 --> 20:19.020
No.

20:20.150 --> 20:21.720
Marge, isn't life funny?

20:21.780 --> 20:23.110
One day, they're babies

20:23.180 --> 20:24.880
the next thing you know,
they're off on their own.

20:25.950 --> 20:27.880
( <i>doorbell )</i>

20:27.960 --> 20:29.690
Are you the man
who reported the lost baby?

20:29.760 --> 20:30.390
Yes.

20:30.460 --> 20:31.460
Can you describe her?

20:31.530 --> 20:33.500
Uh, she's small...

20:33.560 --> 20:34.830
she's a girl...

20:34.900 --> 20:35.830
Bingo!

20:35.900 --> 20:36.870
Oh, Maggie!

20:36.930 --> 20:38.640
Not so fast.

20:38.700 --> 20:40.870
You're wanted on three counts
of criminal neglect.

20:40.940 --> 20:44.740
You found my baby!
Oh, thank you,
thank you, thank you!

20:44.810 --> 20:46.740
( <i>embarrassed chuckling )</i>

20:46.810 --> 20:50.050
Just don't do it again,
you big lug.

20:50.110 --> 20:52.020
( <i>grunting )</i>

20:52.080 --> 20:53.980
You're not going anywhere.

21:02.160 --> 21:04.800
( <i>grunting )</i>

21:17.570 --> 21:19.380
Hi! Did you miss me?

21:19.440 --> 21:21.380
( <i>all talking at once )</i>

21:21.440 --> 21:24.140
Homer:
Never leave again!
Never leave again!

21:24.210 --> 21:25.150
Never leave again.

21:25.210 --> 21:27.410
I missed you too.

21:27.480 --> 21:29.020
Marge:
<i>And from now on,
I hope you'll help me out</i>

21:29.080 --> 21:30.210
<i>a little more than you used to.</i>

21:30.280 --> 21:31.650
You got it, sweetheart.

21:31.720 --> 21:33.320
You have enough blanket, there?

21:33.390 --> 21:35.630
Well, I could use a little more.

21:35.690 --> 21:38.730
And sometimes,
I want a little time to myself

21:38.790 --> 21:40.090
and I expect you to help...

21:40.160 --> 21:41.160
Bart:
Mom...

21:41.230 --> 21:42.470
I think I speak

21:42.530 --> 21:44.270
for everyone
in this bed

21:44.330 --> 21:46.740
when I say you have
<i>nothing to worry about.</i>

21:46.800 --> 21:48.070
Now, let's just
try and get

21:48.140 --> 21:49.640
a little shut-eye. Okay?

21:49.700 --> 21:51.770
( <i>all sighing )</i>

21:58.510 --> 22:02.280
Captioned by
The Caption Center
WGBH Educational Foundation

22:47.260 --> 22:47.830
Shh!
